            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35411",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Unless I'm missing something, this is the expected behavior. \r\n\r\nIf the address is not resolvable (as in this case, at least according to the error message), there's nothing Zend_Http_Client can do (it's not a 404 error - it's not in the HTTP level).\r\n\r\nThe best practice is to wrap your code in a try \/ catch clause:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$url='http:\/\/domain.com';\r\n$client = new Zend_Http_Client($url, array('maxredirects' => 0));\r\ntry {\r\n  $response = $client->request('GET');\r\n  if (!$response) :\r\n  \/\/ ...\r\n} catch (Zend_Http_Client_Adapter_Exception $e) {\r\n  \/\/ handle the error\r\n}\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
